Business Brief -- Schwartz Brothers Inc.:
   Firm Files for Chapter 11
   After Lender Calls In Loans
James Schwartz, president, said the distributor of video
and audio products is "actively engaged" in negotiations to
sell the remaining audio business to another major
distributor. "I believe an agreement is imminent," he said.
The company had already arranged to sell its video business
to a video distributor due to "serious cash flow problems."
   For the nine months ended Oct. 31, Schwartz had a loss of
$2.5 million, or $1.42 a share, on revenue of $60.5 million.